{
  "slug": "was-2019-the-best-movie-year-of-the-decade-plus-the-rise-of-",
  "title": "Was 2019 the Best Movie Year of the Decade? Plus: 'The Rise of Skywalker' Aftermath. | The Oscars Show",
  "show": "The Big Picture",
  "network": "The Ringer",
  "hosts": [
    "Sean Fennessey",
    "Amanda Dobbins"
  ],
  "published": "2019-12-30",
  "runtimeMin": 60,
  "format": "Sean and Amanda do a full-spoilers autopsy of 'The Rise of Skywalker' and the culture war that shaped it, run down Barack Obama's best-of-2019 list, and argue over whether 2019 or 2017 was the best movie year of the decade.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker",
      "note": "full spoilers, and the J.J. Abrams-Rian Johnson culture war",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Amanda's verdict: it's not a good movie, with no stakes and no real respect for how plotting works, though she says she wasn't mad about it, exactly. Sean was really disappointed, and pins the movie's fan-service panic on Kathleen Kennedy needing to land safely between $1 and $1.5 billion. Both flag it as a direct retreat from 'The Last Jedi' backlash, with Chris Terrio erasing Rian Johnson's 'Rey is nobody' twist by making her Palpatine's granddaughter. It scored a B+ CinemaScore, the franchise's lowest since the prequels, and is trailing 'The Last Jedi' at the box office. Amanda still liked where they landed Rey by the end, even if the plane took two hours to get there."
        },
        {
          "title": "Star Wars: The Last Jedi",
          "year": 2017,
          "note": "The film 'Rise of Skywalker' is reacting against. Sean and Amanda trace how its polarized reception, and the vitriol aimed at Kelly Marie Tran, pushed J.J. Abrams and Disney to retrofit most of what Rian Johnson did."
        },
        {
          "title": "Knives Out",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Rian Johnson's other 2019 movie, a genuine hit past the $100 million mark while 'Rise of Skywalker' online discourse rages around him. Sean says he's earned the right not to gloat."
        },
        {
          "title": "Star Wars: The Force Awakens",
          "year": 2015,
          "note": "The Abrams film that restarted the saga; Amanda notes it's the reason he was back in the director's chair to close it out."
        },
        {
          "title": "Solo: A Star Wars Story",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Cited as the franchise's box-office stumble."
        },
        {
          "title": "Rogue One: A Star Wars Story",
          "year": 2016,
          "note": "The counterexample: it did very well, though Sean says the production was famously rocky."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Hark: the Kylo Ren-Rey kiss",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker",
          "note": "Amanda's Hark is aimed at the Kylo Ren-Rey kiss, which she calls the most offensive thing she's seen in the movies this year. Her case: Rey spent the trilogy as a Jedi who wasn't defined by a romance, and a psychic Force bond didn't need to end in a soft kiss to mean something."
        }
      ]
    },
